column5: Got back from Minaki monday night. Fishing was unreal. Started thursday morning and ended monday at noon. Two of us fished 5 to 6 hours a day and when nice my wife would come along. We caught over 80 walleyes between 20 and 29 inches. Not alot of smaller ones. We caught all the slots we wanted to eat. My wife caught the last fish of the trip--29inches, 10lbs 2oz. What a great fishery.
Thanks for the report. Sounds like you had a great trip with a lot of big Walleyes. Where did you catch most of them and what did you use?
mostly all in gunn lake with a bottom bouncer, plane hook and a leech in 25 to 32 ft. of water.
